						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in front of the village office.</p>						

						<p>1824 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Fasli 1234, Tāraṇa, Āsvija śu. 5. The said Fasli might be Sūr-san. The date may be equated to 1824 A.D., September 27.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the conquest of Kellūr by the Kumpaṇi-sarakāra, i.e., East India Company.</p>						

						</summary>
